wikipedia_page.main: George Little (1 December 1915 – March 2002) was an English professional footballer who played as a winger in the Football League for Doncaster Rovers and York City, in non-League football for Throckley Welfare, Scunthorpe United, Frickley Colliery and Worksop Town.
